HB 811 Original 2026 Regular Session Taylor
Abstract: Allows for the consideration of domestic abuse arrest records for the purposes
of setting bail in a domestic abuse case when the domestic abuse arrests did not
result in a conviction.
Present law provides for factors which shall be considered for the purposes of setting bail.
Present law lists one of those factors as "The previous criminal record of the defendant."
Proposed law adds the arrest records of the defendant which alleged domestic abuse battery
within the previous five years but did not result in a conviction.
(Amends C.Cr.P. Art. 316(4)-(10); Adds C.Cr.P. Art. 316(11))
